response:
Let $p,$ $q,$ $r,$ $s$ be the roots of $3x^4-x+12=0$.</think>
Assistant: We are i just given that roots p, q, r, s satisfy the following equation
\[3x^{4} - x +12 =0\]
Ratio of 2nd coefficient to constant is
\[\frac{-1}{12}=\frac{-b}{a}=\frac{-F(1)}{F(0)}\]
So, by the Ruffini-Horner Algorithm( also known as synthetic division ) we can find the sum of the product of roots taken 3 at at time (which is what was asked)
\begin{tabular}{r|l|l}
\multicolumn{5}{l}{F(x) = 3x^{4} - x +12} \\
\cline{2-3}
1 & 3 & 0 & 0 & -1 & 12 \\
 &   & 3 &  3 &  3 & 2 & 0 \\
\cline{2-3}
 & 3 & 3 & 3 & 2 & \boxed{14} \\
\end{tabular}
\emph{1 x 14 = \boxed{14}}

